The paper discusses the use of artificial intelligence in blockchain networks to solve consensus problems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a specific convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the drawbacks of current consensus protocols, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
